subject: p11512104
Findings: Moderate enlargement of the cardiac silhouette is again noted, unchanged. The aorta is mildly tortuous and demonstrates mild atherosclerotic calcification. Hilar contours are within normal limits. Previous pattern of mild interstitial pulmonary edema has nearly completely resolved, with no focal consolidation, pleural effusion or pneumothorax identified. There are multilevel degenerative changes in the thoracic spine, with slight loss of height of a low thoracic/upper lumbar vertebral body, unchanged. Multiple clips in the upper abdomen are unchanged.
Impression: Interval resolution in previous pattern of interstitial pulmonary edema. No radiographic evidence for pneumonia.
